verbose_text: We evaluated 1) the serum levels of lipid markers, CTRP-9 and ADPN fractions, the renal function of the transplanted organs, and the aortic calcification area index (ACAI); 2) the correlations between serum levels of CTRP-9 and ADPN fractions, and vascular calcification; and 3) the correlations between the serum level of CTRP-9 and HMW-ADPN fraction or lipid markers and allograft function (estimated glomerular filtration rate, eGFR) at the start (2008) and the end (2016) of the study period.
